name: Mapbox Streets v7

fields.class: One of: agriculture, cemetery, glacier, grass, hospital, industrial, park, parking, piste, pitch, rock, sand, school, scrub, wood, aboriginal lands
fields.type: OSM tag, more specific than class

fields.class: One of: river, canal, stream, stream_intermittent, ditch, drain
fields.type: One of: river, canal, stream, ditch, drain

fields.class: One of: fence, hedge, cliff, gate

fields.underground: Text. Whether building is underground. One of: 'true', 'false'

fields.type: OSM tag, more specific than class

fields.layer: Number. Specifies z-ordering in the case of overlapping road segments. Common range is -5 to 5. Available from zoom level 13+.
fields.oneway: Text. Whether traffic on the road is one-way. One of: 'true', 'false'
fields.structure: Text. One of: 'none', 'bridge', 'tunnel', 'ford'. Available from zoom level 13+.
fields.type: In most cases, values will be that of the primary key from OpenStreetMap tags.

fields.admin_level: The OSM administrative level of the boundary
fields.disputed: Number. Disputed boundaries are 1, all others are 0.
fields.iso_3166_1: The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 code(s) of the state(s) a boundary is part of. Format: 'AA' or 'AA-BB'
fields.maritime: Number. Maritime boundaries are 1, all others are 0.

fields.name: Local name of the country
fields.parent: ISO 3166-1 Alpha-2 code of the administering/parent state, if any
fields.scalerank: Number, 1-6. Useful for styling text sizes.
fields.type: One of: country, territory, disputed territory, sar

fields.labelrank: Number, 1-6. Useful for styling text sizes.
fields.name: Local or international name of the water body
fields.name_de: German name of the water body
fields.name_en: English name of the water body
fields.name_es: Spanish name of the water body
fields.name_fr: French name of the water body
fields.name_ru: Russian name of the water body
fields.name_zh: Chinese name of the water body

fields.area: The area of the state in kilometers²
fields.name: Local name of the state

fields.capital: Admin level the city is a capital of, if any. One of: 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, null
fields.ldir: A hint for label placement at low zoom levels. One of: N, E, S, W, NE, SE, SW, NW, null
fields.localrank: Number. Priority relative to nearby places. Useful for limiting label density.
fields.name: Local name of the place
fields.scalerank: Number, 0-9 or null. Useful for styling text & marker sizes.
fields.type: One of: city, town, village, hamlet, suburb, neighbourhood, island, islet, archipelago, residential, aboriginal_lands

fields.area: The area of the water polygon in Mercator meters²
fields.name: Local name of the water body
fields.name_de: German name of the water body
fields.name_en: English name of the water body
fields.name_es: Spanish name of the water body
fields.name_fr: French name of the water body
fields.name_ru: Russian name of the water body
fields.name_zh: Chinese name of the water body

fields.maki: One of: airport, airfield, heliport, rocket
fields.name: Local name of the airport
fields.ref: A 3-4 character IATA, FAA, ICAO, or other reference code
fields.scalerank: Number 1-4. Useful for styling icon sizes.

fields.maki: One of: rail, rail-metro, rail-light, entrance
fields.name: Local name of the station
fields.network: The network(s) that the station serves. Useful for icon styling.

fields.localrank: Number. Priority relative to nearby POIs. Useful for limiting label density.
fields.maki: The name of the Maki icon that should be used for the POI
fields.name: Local name of the POI
fields.scalerank: Number. 1-5. Useful for styling icon sizes and minimum zoom levels.

fields.class: The class of road the junction is on. Matches the classes in the road layer.
fields.name: A longer name
fields.reflen: The number of characters in the ref field.
fields.type: The type of road the junction is on. Matches the types in the road layer.

fields.iso_3166_2: Text. The ISO 3166-2 code of the state/province/region the road is in.
fields.len: Number. Approximate length of the road segment in Mercator meters.
fields.localrank: Number. Used for shield points only. Priority relative to nearby shields. Useful for limiting shield density.
fields.name: Local name of the road
fields.reflen: Number. How many characters long the ref tag is. Useful for shield styling.
fields.shield: The shield style to use. One of: default, mx-federal, mx-state, us-highway, us-highway-alternate, us-highway-business, us-highway-duplex, us-interstate, us-interstate-business, us-interstate-duplex, us-interstate-truck, us-state

fields.class: One of: river, canal, stream, stream_intermittent
fields.name: Local name of the waterway
